<br>
But... 8 points is a lot to spend just for a tactical advantage over Hunters, Scouts, and the occasional Minstrel.  It doesn't do anything for my offensive power or my defensive ability, both of which could use a boost.  That 8 points could be second level Dodger and faster attacks, second level Wild Arcana, 8/9ths of second level First Aid, etc.<br>
<br>
Any other pros or cons?  Has anyone else decided whether or not you're getting it? <p><b>Ciardha Sidhe</b>, Elven Nightshade of Guinevere<br><small>&quot;The sword cuts both ways... but not at the same time.&quot;</small></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uditherdaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dither DAoC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/7/02 9:33:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=188.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/dither/smiley2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: See Hidden... worth it?</span><hr size=1> if see hidden and truesight stay exactly how they are on pendragon, i am definitly putting my first 8 points into this.  it is far to valuable to me to pass up.  i dont have 2 spell abilities to possibly choose to put points into though, so im not at the same point handicap nightshades are.<br>
